Definition and Scope
The Anti-Money Laundering (AML) market refers to the range of products, services, and technologies designed to combat money laundering and ensure compliance with regulations aimed at preventing financial crimes. Money laundering is the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. AML efforts are crucial for maintaining the integrity of the financial system and protecting economies from criminal activities.
As per Intent Market Research, the Anti-Money Laundering Market was valued at USD 2.9 billion in 2023-e and will surpass USD 8.6 billion by 2030; growing at a CAGR of 16.5% during 2024 - 2030.
